The paper focuses on machine learning methods for brain tumor image analysis, specifically for segmentation, progression assessment, and overall survival prediction. This falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of machine learning algorithms for these tasks also suggests artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of multi-parametric magnetic resonance imaging (mpMRI) scans, which involves signal processing and image retrieval techniques, indicating the possibility of sub-categories such as neural networks and deep learning (cs.NE) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
